5. Core Service Portfolio
5.1 Trust & Identity (T&I)
eduroam: Global secure Wi-Fi roaming for academics. Authenticates billions of sessions annually.

eduGAIN: Interfederation service connecting 70+ identity federations, allowing users to use home credentials for thousands of services.

InAcademia: Real-time student/staff status verification for commercial discounts and services.

5.2 Cloud Services (OCRE)
OCRE 2024 Framework: The current framework (active from Feb 2025 to 2030) providing compliant access to commercial cloud services (AWS, Google, Azure) with pre-negotiated volume discounts and data-egress waivers.

5.3 Security
GÉANT Security Days: Annual community event for cybersecurity practitioners.

DDoS Mitigation: Infrastructure-level protection for the European backbone and member NRENs.

6. Research & Innovation Role
GÉANT tests emerging technologies before they hit the commercial market.

Quantum Networking: Testing Quantum Key Distribution (QKD) and ultra-precise time/frequency transfer.

Fibre Sensing: Using the fiber backbone to detect environmental events (e.g., plane landings, seismic activity).

AI for Networks (AIOps): Using machine learning to predict outages and optimize traffic flow.

